# The Grammarly extension and the fact that it can become active while learners take the PW. We have inquired about this with Learnosity a few times, and this was the most recent communication with them, back in November. They offered this possible solution:

 

And I'd like to add one more thing in case it helps. One of our engineers looked at how Grammarly manipulates the DOM to support its extension, and suggested a way that your developers could pursue blocking it dynamically. 
 
If this approach works out of the box, great. If not, it may require minor tweaking to work. But it's essential to understand that these are features offered by Grammarly as a way of supporting their product. It's entirely possible that Grammarly could change these techniques regularly to avoid blocking (much the way Google continues to try to prevent ad blockers from working every time a new approach is invented by a third party).
 
[Here is a Gist|https://gist.github.com/michaelsharman/bb579c287048b14d98a35cd59a1fbcc1] that removes data attributes that Grammarly adds to DOM elements like input boxes. Here's a brief excerpt to show what I mean:

{noformat}$els[i].setAttribute('data-gramm', 'false');

$els[i].setAttribute('data-gramm_editor', 'false');

$els[i].setAttribute('data-enable-grammarly', 'false');{noformat}

 
This can be invoked after reacting to a Learnosity event, as shown in the Gist, which means you can block Grammarly when using a Learnosity assessment, but not at other times so the end user's computer will not be adversely affected.
 
At the risk of frustration, I must firmly reiterate that this workaround is based around removing the DOM manipulations that Grammarly injects to enable its functionality. This is outside our control, and this workaround is entirely unsupported. For example, if this version of the Gist doesn't work any longer due to changes Grammarly has made since, we won't be able to address this further. However, it may help you get where you need to go if you feel that blocking Grammarly is achievable with custom code.

